</table>
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{atode}}}} can be used after a noun that indicates an event.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{attend^matter}}no@EM{{atode}},@KJ{{drink}}mini@KJ{{going}}kimasenka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Shall we go and have a drink after work?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
When the main clause contains words such as @HI{{iru}} or @HI{{aru}}, @HI{{@EM{{atode}}}} sounds awkward and @HI{{@EM{{ato}}}} should be used.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{impart^profession}}:jugyou}}ga@KJ{{finish}}watta@EM{{ato}},@KJ{{study^life}}ga2,3@KJ{{person}}mada@KJ{{teach^room}}ni@FG{{@KJ{{remainder}}:noko}}tteimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
